 "remarks": "Nestled on one of Noroton Heights&apos; most sought-after streets, this sun-drenched coastal charmer seamlessly blends classic appeal with thoughtful modern updates. With newly renovated bathrooms, a new deck, and beautifully refinished hardwood floors, this home captures the essence of Darien living with an enviable walk-to-everything location. The fully fenced, level backyard has been lovingly landscaped, creating a private outdoor retreat ideal for entertaining, play, or simply relaxing. The lower level expands the home&apos;s living space with 440 square feet of finished recreational area. An adjoining unfinished space provides a dedicated laundry area and abundant storage, bringing the total lower-level footprint to approximately 800 square feet per the tax card. Enjoy an unbeatable location just a short walk to the Noroton Heights train station, Darien Commons, and Heights Crossing, where you&apos;ll find an array of restaurants, cafes, boutiques, and everyday conveniences. With easy access to I-95 and close proximity to Middlesex Middle School and Darien High School, this special property offers the perfect balance of neighborhood charm and modern convenience. Don&apos;t miss the opportunity to make this gem of a house your new home.",
